Respect to neighbors is highly expected.

Since cleanliness of the apartment is one of my top priorities for this place, walking with shoes /slippers inside the apartment is not allowed. 

No partying, no loud music please.

Strictly no smoking inside the room / apartment / building. Violation to the non-smoking policy will result to penalty or fine of $250 USD.

Please do not lose keys. Lost keys keys incur $75 fee for replacement.

Make sure lock door when you go ou of the apartment t for our safety.

No other guests allowed other than people who reserved the place. 

Please keep the room and apartment clean and in order.

Please keep clean bathroom and free of dirt. Please maintain its cleanliness for everyone.

Please do not use towels to remove facial make-up.

Please turn off bathroom and your room's lights when you go out.

Please keep in mind the check in and out times. 

Finally, enjoy your stay!! :)
description:
This apartment is a real 2 bedroom place that is cozy, clean and immaculate. Only 2 short blocks from the NYC "6"subway train which is at 103rd St.  Station literally a 1 minute walk! Building is within walking distance to Central Park!! Close to shops, markets, great restaurants, laundry, deli, etc. Safe neighborhood. The train takes and connects you to the main tourists' spots you can ever think of. Quality beddings and fresh towels provided.

This apartment has real two luxury-like bedrooms.  One room has comfortable queen-sized bed while the other room has a full-sized bed. Both are very cozy, clean and comfortable. Very modern, clean and cozy. It has big windows and street views.  It has its own immaculate full bathroom, a kitchen and a decent living comfy living space. The beddings are of great quality and are always fresh. Bath stuff such as shampoo, soap, etc. are also provided. The kitchen is equipped with basic cookware for light cooking and dining wares and utensils.

Guests have access to the building and the entire apartment (please give special attention to the listing rules though. Thank you).

I love meeting with guests and helping them during their stay when needed. I respect their privacy as always. I will be reachable during their stay personally or through phone or via Airbnb messaging or various Apps. I can also be reached before arrival so I can help out in guests' planning, arrival and during their trip.

I love the diversity in this neighborhood. It has almost everything a guest would want -- restaurants, shops, grocery / market, convenience stores, laundry shops, pharmacy. The famous Central Park is only a few blocks from my place. It is within walking distance.  Everything is close to my building. Restaurants are literally a minute walk from my apartment door.  24-laundry area is also right at the next block. Convenience stores and groceries are within walking distance.  Your stay here will definitely give you a feeling of being a "local" in the beautiful city of Manhattan!!

There are two options for train / subway to go around the Big Apple. There is one at 96th Street or at 103rd Street. The train is the Train 6 which runs on the Green line - both directions. It goes and connects you to the main tourists' spots such as:

Times Square
Grand Central
Brooklyn Bridge
Statue of Liberty
Empire State Building
Union Square
Little Italy / China Town / SOHO
Southstreet Seaport
Chelsea
Hells Kitchen
The Museums
86th Street Shopping Complex

Also my place is within walking distance to the popular Central Park!!!
